Summary:
# Mystic Vaults

These are items storing multiple items. Vaults have 3 layers:
1. the top layer with two relatively weak items like potions
2. the middle layer with two stronger items for protection or persistent strengths
3. the bottom layer with the strongest, usually destructive item.

You can pick one item from the highest layer of the vault that has any items in it. Regardless of whether you pick an item, the vault will pass automatically to another player after the night you have the item. The dangerous item at the bottom will therefore only be available N5 at the earliest, if every previous owner has picked an item from the vault. Vaults cannot be stolen or destroyed, but they disappear when empty :)

## The vaults' whereabouts
N1 the following players claim to have had a Mystic Vault:
- KillerClown;
- Gandorb;
- FirstKill;
- NotYourBropher;
- DutchDiddler.

Because of the vaults' auto-pass mechanic it should be possible to figure out where they are at any given point. *KillerClown* says that If a vault holder gets killed, the vault goes to the GY with them and then is passed back to the living the next night. I can't confirm that because I struggled with the wording at that point.

## Strategies
I think it's important to talk about different ways to handle the vaults. So far we've had two: 
- One strategy can be to not take any items from the vault so that the dangerous items at the bottom stay inaccessible. This is what *KillerClown* aimed to do.
- Another strategy is to take an item from the vault every night so that the dangerous items can be tied to more or less certain players. This is what I (*FirstKill*) tried to do. *Gandorb* also took an item.

## I love this new item!
It adds a whole new layer to the game. It is strategic, involves a lot of players given the number and the auto-passes, and gives hints about the setup.
I am Vigilant with a Wolf Pelt. I think I'm meant to try to horde the bad items to prevent the Evils from getting them.

Summary:
# Mystic Vaults

These are items storing multiple items. Vaults have 3 layers:
1. the top layer with two relatively weak items like potions
2. the middle layer with two stronger items for protection or persistent strengths
3. the bottom layer with the strongest, usually destructive item.

You can pick one item from the highest layer of the vault that has any items in it. Regardless of whether you pick an item, the vault will pass automatically to another player after the night you have the item. The dangerous item at the bottom will therefore only be available N5 at the earliest, if every previous owner has picked an item from the vault. Vaults cannot be stolen or destroyed, but they disappear when empty :)

## The vaults' whereabouts
N1 the following players claim to have had a Mystic Vault:
- KillerClown;
- Gandorb;
- FirstKill;
- NotYourBropher;
- DutchDiddler
- DjinnTonic. 

Because of the vaults' auto-pass mechanic it should be possible to figure out where they are at any given point. *KillerClown* says that If a vault holder gets killed, the vault goes to the GY with them and then is passed back to the living the next night. I can't confirm that because I struggled with the wording at that point.

## Strategies
I think it's important to talk about different ways to handle the vaults. So far we've had two: 
- One strategy can be to not take any items from the vault so that the dangerous items at the bottom stay inaccessible. This is what *KillerClown* aimed to do.
- Another strategy is to take an item from the vault every night so that the dangerous items can be tied to more or less certain players. This is what I (*FirstKill*) tried to do. *Gandorb* also took an item.
- We should also consider that giving the exact  contents of the vaults will allow evils who have changed avatar to pretend they had the vaults when it was their turn. 

## I love this new item!
It adds a whole new layer to the game. It is strategic, involves a lot of players given the number and the auto-passes, and gives hints about the setup.

# Mystic Vaults

Vaults have 3 layers:
1. the top layer with two relatively weak items like potions
2. the middle layer with two stronger items for protection or persistent strengths
3. the bottom layer with the strongest item.

You can pick one item from the highest layer of the vault that has any items in it. Regardless of whether you pick an item, the vault will pass automatically to the next player in the list of living players after the night you have the item. The item at the bottom will therefore only be available N5 at the earliest, if every previous owner has picked an item from the vault. Vaults cannot be stolen or destroyed, but they disappear when empty.

## The vaults' whereabouts
N1 the following players claim to have had a Mystic Vault:
- KillerClown;
- Gandorb;
- FirstKill;
- NotYourBropher;
- DutchDiddler
- DjinnTonic;
- DivinerOnStrike;
- SinceUBeenGone;
- **WargTF** (according to BillBangedAss, D3 09:28);
- **BillBangedAss** (according to MasonBrother D3 09:02);
- MasonBrother (D3 09:38).

Because of the auto-pass mechanic it should be possible to figure out where they are at any given point. *KillerClown* says that If a vault holder gets killed, the vault goes to the GY with them and then is passed back to the living the next night. I can't confirm that because I struggled with the wording at that point. *BillBangedAss* could help here by saying clearly if they started with a vault or got one N2.

## Strategies
I think it's important to talk about different ways to handle the vaults. So far we've had two: 
- One strategy can be to not take any items from the vault so that the dangerous items at the bottom stay inaccessible. This is what *KillerClown* aimed to do.
- Another strategy is to take an item from the vault every night so that the dangerous items can be tied to more or less certain players. This is what I (*FirstKill*) tried to do. *Gandorb* also took an item.
- We should also consider that giving the exact  contents of the vaults will allow evils who have changed avatar to pretend they had the vaults when it was their turn. 

## I love this new item!
It adds a whole new layer to the game. It is strategic, involves a lot of players given the number and the auto-passes, and gives hints about the setup.

# Conflict between Bill and Mason
*MasonBrother* claims to have started with a vault (D3 09:38) and to have received a vault N2 (D3 09:02). This should have come from *BillBangedAss*, but Bill claims he only received his vault N2 (D3 09:28). He clarifies (D3 11:38) he didn't start with one.

*DjinnTonic* claims Mason's N2 vault came from them (D3 12:05); they tried to pass it manually and think this worked because of the trinket they started with. But if this theory is not true, the vault would have passed to *NotYourBropher*. They got killed N2, so can't confirm the theory.

Mason has specified the contents of his two vaults in his summary on D3 10:28:05:

N1: Mystic Vault:
1. Dagger of Paranoia, Steal Potion
2. (Ankh of Resurrection), (Ethereal Armour)
3. ((Iron Collar))
- Nothing Taken

N2: Mystic Vault:
1. 2x Potion of Protection
2. (Manacles), (Disruption Orb)
3. ((Warg's Bracer))
- Nothing Taken

# Mystic Vaults

Vaults have 3 layers:
1. the top layer with two relatively weak items like potions
2. the middle layer with two stronger items for protection or persistent strengths
3. the bottom layer with the strongest item.

You can pick one item from the highest layer of the vault that has any items in it. Regardless of whether you pick an item, the vault will pass automatically to the next player in the list of living players after the night you have the item. The item at the bottom will therefore only be available N5 at the earliest, if every previous owner has picked an item from the vault. Vaults cannot be stolen or destroyed, but they disappear when empty.

## The vaults' whereabouts
N1 the following players claim to have had a Mystic Vault:
- KillerClown;
- Gandorb;
- FirstKill;
- NotYourBropher;
- DutchDiddler
- DjinnTonic;
- DivinerOnStrike;
- SinceUBeenGone;
- **WargTF** (according to BillBangedAss, D3 09:28);
- **BillBangedAss** (according to MasonBrother D3 09:02, later claimed to be DjinnTonic's N1 vault 12:05);
- MasonBrother (D3 09:38).

Because of the auto-pass mechanic it should be possible to figure out where they are at any given point. *KillerClown* says that If a vault holder gets killed, the vault goes to the GY with them and then is passed back to the living the next night. I can't confirm that because I struggled with the wording at that point. *BillBangedAss* could help here by saying clearly if they started with a vault or got one N2.

## Strategies
I think it's important to talk about different ways to handle the vaults. So far we've had two: 
- One strategy can be to not take any items from the vault so that the dangerous items at the bottom stay inaccessible. This is what *KillerClown* aimed to do.
- Another strategy is to take an item from the vault every night so that the dangerous items can be tied to more or less certain players. This is what I (*FirstKill*) tried to do. *Gandorb* also took an item.
- We should also consider that giving the exact  contents of the vaults will allow evils who have changed avatar to pretend they had the vaults when it was their turn. 

## I love this new item!
It adds a whole new layer to the game. It is strategic, involves a lot of players given the number and the auto-passes, and gives hints about the setup.

Summary:
#Claims
- Deadies: Pollygrapher
- Bill: Militia
- Mark: Crypt Thief
- Gandorb: Psychic
- Cereal: Curator
- FirstKill: Pagan
- Clown: Villager
- Succubish: Drunk Harlot
- DivinerOnStrike: Inebriated Seer (D4 18:5x)

# The vaults' whereabouts
N1 the following players claim to have had a Mystic Vault:
- FirstKill (claimed D2); confirmed by Succubish and DefaultExecution
- Gandorb (claimed D2); confirmed by DivinerOnStrike, Deadies (but not number of items)
- DivinerOnStrike (claimed D3); confirmed by Deadies (4 items)
- **WargTF**; claimed by BillBangedAss, D3 09:28);
- MasonBrother (D3 09:38); confirmed by DjinnTonic
- DjinnTonic (claimed D2); passed owing to trinket, confirmed by MasonBrother
- NotYourBropher (claimed D2); died N2;  vault confirmed by CerealDestroyer;
- SinceUBeenGone; confirmed D4 by *Parrot* (ex KillerClown) **but with a mistake in the bottom tier item that suggests Parrot got it from *DutchDiddler* who preceded his new position in the list**
- KillerClown (claimed D2); N2 changed to Parrot and moved to last position in the list; ??confirmed by *DutchDiddler*?? and DoingADobby
- DutchDiddler; confirmed by DoingADobby (4 items, D4 13:0x) and DefinitelyVanilla (4 items).

Because of the auto-pass mechanic it should be possible to figure out where they are at any given point. *KillerClown* says that If a vault holder gets killed, the vault goes to the GY with them and then is passed back to the living the next night. I can't confirm that because I struggled with the wording at that point. 

## Unusual vault moves between Djinn and Mason
*MasonBrother* claims to have started with a vault (D3 09:38) and to have received a vault N2 (D3 09:02). This should have come from *BillBangedAss*, but Bill claims he only received his vault N2 (D3 09:28). He clarifies (D3 11:38) he didn't start with one.

*DjinnTonic* claims Mason's N2 vault came from them (D3 12:05); they tried to pass it manually and think this worked because of the trinket they started with. But if this theory is not true, the vault would have passed to *NotYourBropher*. They got killed N2, so can't confirm the theory.

Mason has specified the contents of his two vaults in his summary on D3 10:28:05:

N1: Mystic Vault:
1. Dagger of Paranoia, Steal Potion
2. (Ankh of Resurrection), (Ethereal Armour)
3. ((Iron Collar))
- Nothing Taken

N2: Mystic Vault:
1. 2x Potion of Protection
2. (Manacles), (Disruption Orb)
3. ((Warg's Bracer))
- Nothing Taken

## Strategies
I think it's important to talk about different ways to handle the vaults. So far we've had two: 
- One strategy can be to not take any items from the vault so that the dangerous items at the bottom stay inaccessible. This is what *KillerClown* aimed to do.
- Another strategy is to take an item from the vault every night so that the dangerous items can be tied to more or less certain players. This is what I (*FirstKill*) tried to do. *Gandorb* also took an item.
- We should also consider that giving the exact  contents of the vaults will allow evils who have changed avatar to pretend they had the vaults when it was their turn. 

## I love this new item!
It adds a whole new layer to the game. It is strategic, involves a lot of players given the number and the auto-passes, and gives hints about the setup.

- FirstKill (claimed D2); confirmed by Succubish and DefaultExecution
- Gandorb (claimed D2); confirmed by DivinerOnStrike, Deadies (but not number of items)
- DivinerOnStrike (claimed D3); confirmed by Deadies (4 items)
- **WargTF**; claimed by BillBangedAss, D3 09:28);
- MasonBrother (D3 09:38); confirmed by DjinnTonic
- DjinnTonic (claimed D2); passed owing to trinket, confirmed by MasonBrother
- NotYourBropher (claimed D2); died N2;  vault confirmed by CerealDestroyer;
- SinceUBeenGone; confirmed D4 by *Parrot* (ex KillerClown) **but with a mistake in the bottom tier item that suggests Parrot got it from *DutchDiddler* who preceded his new position in the list**
- KillerClown (claimed D2); N2 changed to Parrot and moved to last position in the list; ??confirmed by *DutchDiddler*?? and DoingADobby

I can't confirm that because I struggled with the wording at that point. 

## Unusual vault moves between Djinn and Mason
*MasonBrother* claims to have started with a vault (D3 09:38) and to have received a vault N2 (D3 09:02). This should have come from *BillBangedAss*, but Bill claims he only received his vault N2 (D3 09:28). He clarifies (D3 11:38) he didn't start with one.

*DjinnTonic* claims Mason's N2 vault came from them (D3 12:05); they tried to pass it manually and think this worked because of the trinket they started with. But if this theory is not true, the vault would have passed to *NotYourBropher*. They got killed N2, so can't confirm the theory.

Mason has specified the contents of his two vaults in his summary on D3 10:28:05:

N1: Mystic Vault:
1. Dagger of Paranoia, Steal Potion
2. (Ankh of Resurrection), (Ethereal Armour)
3. ((Iron Collar))
- Nothing Taken

N2: Mystic Vault:
1. 2x Potion of Protection
2. (Manacles), (Disruption Orb)
3. ((Warg's Bracer))
- Nothing Taken

## Strategies
I think it's important to talk about different ways to handle the vaults. So far we've had two: 
- One strategy can be to not take any items from the vault so that the dangerous items at the bottom stay inaccessible. This is what *KillerClown* aimed to do.
- Another strategy is to take an item from the vault every night so that the dangerous items can be tied to more or less certain players. This is what I (*FirstKill*) tried to do. *Gandorb* also took an item.
- We should also consider that giving the exact  contents of the vaults will allow evils who have changed avatar to pretend they had the vaults when it was their turn. 

## I love this new item!
It adds a whole new layer to the game. It is strategic, involves a lot of players given the number and the auto-passes, and gives hints about the setup.

# The vaults' whereabouts
N1 the following players claim to have had a Mystic Vault:
- FirstKill (claimed D2); confirmed by Succubish and DefaultExecution
- Gandorb (claimed D2); confirmed by DivinerOnStrike, Deadies (but not number of items)
- DivinerOnStrike (claimed D3); confirmed by Deadies (4 items)

- DjinnTonic (claimed D2); passed owing to trinket, confirmed by MasonBrother

- SinceUBeenGone; confirmed D4 by *Parrot* (ex KillerClown) **but with a mistake in the bottom tier item that suggests Parrot got it from *DutchDiddler* who preceded his new position in the list**
- KillerClown (claimed D2); N2 changed to Parrot and moved to last position in the list; ??confirmed by *DutchDiddler*?? and DoingADobby
- DutchDiddler; confirmed by DoingADobby (4 items, D4 13:0x) and DefinitelyVanilla (4 items).

Because of the auto-pass mechanic it should be possible to figure out where they are at any given point. *KillerClown* says that If a vault holder gets killed, the vault goes to the GY with them and then is passed back to the living the next night. I can't confirm that because I struggled with the wording at that point. 

## Unusual vault moves between Djinn and Mason
*MasonBrother* claims to have started with a vault (D3 09:38) and to have received a vault N2 (D3 09:02). This should have come from *BillBangedAss*, but Bill claims he only received his vault N2 (D3 09:28). He clarifies (D3 11:38) he didn't start with one.

*DjinnTonic* claims Mason's N2 vault came from them (D3 12:05); they tried to pass it manually and think this worked because of the trinket they started with. But if this theory is not true, the vault would have passed to *NotYourBropher*. They got killed N2, so can't confirm the theory.

Mason has specified the contents of his two vaults in his summary on D3 10:28:05:

N1: Mystic Vault:
1. Dagger of Paranoia, Steal Potion
2. (Ankh of Resurrection), (Ethereal Armour)
3. ((Iron Collar))
- Nothing Taken

N2: Mystic Vault:
1. 2x Potion of Protection
2. (Manacles), (Disruption Orb)
3. ((Warg's Bracer))
- Nothing Taken

## Strategies
I think it's important to talk about different ways to handle the vaults. So far we've had two: 
- One strategy can be to not take any items from the vault so that the dangerous items at the bottom stay inaccessible. This is what *KillerClown* aimed to do.
- Another strategy is to take an item from the vault every night so that the dangerous items can be tied to more or less certain players. This is what I (*FirstKill*) tried to do. *Gandorb* also took an item.
- We should also consider that giving the exact  contents of the vaults will allow evils who have changed avatar to pretend they had the vaults when it was their turn. 

## I love this new item!
It adds a whole new layer to the game. It is strategic, involves a lot of players given the number and the auto-passes, and gives hints about the setup.

# The vaults' whereabouts
N1 the following players claim to have had a Mystic Vault:
- FirstKill (claimed D2); confirmed by Succubish and DefaultExecution
- Gandorb (claimed D2); confirmed by DivinerOnStrike, Deadies (but not number of items)
- DivinerOnStrike (claimed D3); confirmed by Deadies (4 items)

- MasonBrother (D3 09:38); confirmed by DjinnTonic
- DjinnTonic (claimed D2); passed owing to trinket, confirmed by MasonBrother
- NotYourBropher (claimed D2); died N2;  vault confirmed by CerealDestroyer;
- SinceUBeenGone; confirmed D4 by *Parrot* (ex KillerClown) **but with a mistake in the bottom tier item that suggests Parrot got it from *DutchDiddler* who preceded his new position in the list**
- KillerClown (claimed D2); N2 changed to Parrot and moved to last position in the list; ??confirmed by *DutchDiddler*?? and DoingADobby
- DutchDiddler; confirmed by DoingADobby (4 items, D4 13:0x) and DefinitelyVanilla (4 items).

Because of the auto-pass mechanic it should be possible to figure out where they are at any given point. *KillerClown* says that If a vault holder gets killed, the vault goes to the GY with them and then is passed back to the living the next night. I can't confirm that because I struggled with the wording at that point. 

## Unusual vault moves between Djinn and Mason
*MasonBrother* claims to have started with a vault (D3 09:38) and to have received a vault N2 (D3 09:02). This should have come from *BillBangedAss*, but Bill claims he only received his vault N2 (D3 09:28). He clarifies (D3 11:38) he didn't start with one.

*DjinnTonic* claims Mason's N2 vault came from them (D3 12:05); they tried to pass it manually and think this worked because of the trinket they started with. But if this theory is not true, the vault would have passed to *NotYourBropher*. They got killed N2, so can't confirm the theory.

Mason has specified the contents of his two vaults in his summary on D3 10:28:05:

N1: Mystic Vault:
1. Dagger of Paranoia, Steal Potion
2. (Ankh of Resurrection), (Ethereal Armour)
3. ((Iron Collar))
- Nothing Taken

N2: Mystic Vault:
1. 2x Potion of Protection
2. (Manacles), (Disruption Orb)
3. ((Warg's Bracer))
- Nothing Taken

## Strategies
I think it's important to talk about different ways to handle the vaults. So far we've had two: 
- One strategy can be to not take any items from the vault so that the dangerous items at the bottom stay inaccessible. This is what *KillerClown* aimed to do.
- Another strategy is to take an item from the vault every night so that the dangerous items can be tied to more or less certain players. This is what I (*FirstKill*) tried to do. *Gandorb* also took an item.
- We should also consider that giving the exact  contents of the vaults will allow evils who have changed avatar to pretend they had the vaults when it was their turn. 

## I love this new item!
It adds a whole new layer to the game. It is strategic, involves a lot of players given the number and the auto-passes, and gives hints about the setup.
